\section{Introduction}

Let $M$ be an $n-$dimensional semi-Riemannian manifold of $m-$dimensional
semi-Euclidean space $\mathbb{E}_{s}^{m}.$ If a smooth map $\phi $
semi-Riemannian manifold $M$ into semi-Euclidean space can be expressed as
finite sum of eigenfunctions of the Laplacian operator $\Delta $ of $M,$ it
is said to be finite type. If these eigenfunctions are different from each
other and $k$ numbers then the map $\phi $\ is said to be of $k-$type. If
the smooth map $\phi $ is an isometric immersion $x:M\rightarrow \mathbb{E}
_{s}^{m},$ that is, the position vector of $M$ can be written as finite sum
of eigenvectors of the Laplacian $\Delta $ of $M,$ then $M$ is said to be
finite type submanifold. The notion of finite type mapping was introduced by
B.Y.Chen in late 1970's. Because of studying the maps of finite type on
defined on $M$ has become a useful tool in determining of geometrical
properties of submanifold $M,$ many papers have been published in this topic.

The Gauss map $G$ of a submanifold $M$ into $G(n,m)$ in $\wedge ^{n}\mathbb{E
}_{s}^{m},$ where $G(n,m)$ is the Grassmannian manifold consisting of all
oriented $n-$planes through the origin of $\mathbb{E}_{s}^{m}$ and $\wedge
^{n}\mathbb{E}_{s}^{m}$ is the vector space obtained by the exterior product
of $n$ vectors in $\mathbb{E}_{s}^{m}$ is a smooth map which carries a point 
$p$ in $M$ into the oriented $n-$plane in $\mathbb{E}_{s}^{m}$ obtained from
parallel translation of the tangent space of $M$ at $p$ in $\mathbb{E}
_{s}^{m}.$ Since the vector space $\wedge ^{n}\mathbb{E}_{s}^{m}$ identify
with a semi-Euclidean space $\mathbb{E}_{t}^{N}$ for some positive integer $
t,$ where $N=\left( 
\begin{array}{c}
m \\ 
n
\end{array}
\right) ,$ the Gauss map is defined by $G:M\rightarrow G(n,m)\subset \mathbb{
E}_{t}^{N},$ $G(p)=\left( e_{1}\wedge ...\wedge e_{n}\right) \left( p\right)
.$ So, the notion of finite type mappings is naturally extended to Gauss
maps of submanifolds. The notion of submanifolds with finite type Gauss map
was introduced by B. Y.Chen and P.Piccinni in 1987 \cite{chen} and after
then many works were done about this topic, especially 1-type Gauss map and
2- type Gauss map.

